Dilation

Expands the white region in the image (thickens edges).

kernel = np.ones((5,5), np.uint8)
dilated = cv2.dilate(img, kernel, iterations=1)

Erosion

Shrinks the white region (thins edges).

eroded = cv2.erode(img, kernel, iterations=1)


ðŸ‘‰ Often used together in tasks like noise removal.

